WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.742
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

00:03.873 --> 00:05.527
-WHOA!

00:15.537 --> 00:16.581
-WHOA!

00:16.712 --> 00:18.105
-YEAH!

00:21.673 --> 00:24.415
-YEAH! TAKE IT
AROUND AGAIN!

00:31.857 --> 00:33.511
GO FASTER, MAN!

01:02.627 --> 01:03.585
-TAP IT THERE.

01:03.715 --> 01:05.065
-TOP OF THE MORNING TO YA.

01:09.330 --> 01:10.679
WHAT IS HE DOING?

01:11.593 --> 01:14.509
-HE'S LOOKING FOR THE
NEW MISS HOT TAMALE.

01:14.639 --> 01:16.946
-I'D ASK BUT I
DON'T WANNA KNOW.

01:17.077 --> 01:18.121
-I DON'T BLAME YA.

01:20.384 --> 01:21.255
MITCH.

01:22.299 --> 01:26.782
-[SOLEMN MUSIC]

01:32.701 --> 01:34.094
-STRAIGHT, MAN!

01:36.748 --> 01:38.359
-[SHOUTING]

01:39.534 --> 01:41.101
-[SCREAMING]

01:42.798 --> 01:44.234
-CALL FOR BACK UP.

01:44.365 --> 01:45.627
-LOOK'S LIKE BAYGUARD'S
ALREADY ON IT, MAN.

01:45.757 --> 01:47.150
-CALL FOR BACK UP!
-CODY: ALL RIGHT.

01:50.327 --> 01:51.676
HEADQUARTERS,
THIS IS MADISON.

01:51.807 --> 01:53.243
WE GOT A PARASAILOR DOWN.

01:54.026 --> 01:55.941
-MAN: BAYGUARD ONE
RESPONDING TO PARASAILOR

01:56.072 --> 01:58.118
DOWN AT THUMBALY 13-10-4.

02:07.823 --> 02:09.172
-GET THE CANS!

02:22.185 --> 02:24.144
-CONSCIOUS. WATCH
HIS NECK, GO!

02:27.973 --> 02:29.671
-RELAX, BUDDY. I GOT YOU.

02:33.718 --> 02:35.067
-THEY DID IT AGAIN.

02:35.198 --> 02:36.939
-MITCH: HOW'D THEY
GET THERE SO FAST?

02:37.809 --> 02:39.333
-GO ON, GET HIM IN.

02:39.985 --> 02:41.073
-CODY: GOOD QUESTION.

02:46.427 --> 02:49.865
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

02:54.391 --> 02:57.220
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

02:58.178 --> 03:01.790
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

03:01.920 --> 03:05.837
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

03:05.968 --> 03:09.580
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

03:09.711 --> 03:12.061
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

03:12.192 --> 03:14.672
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

03:18.110 --> 03:19.503
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

03:19.634 --> 03:23.681
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

03:26.815 --> 03:28.860
♪ I'LL BE READY

03:28.991 --> 03:30.514
♪ I'LL BE READY

03:30.645 --> 03:32.603
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

03:32.734 --> 03:34.562
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

03:34.692 --> 03:37.826
♪ I'LL BE READY

03:37.956 --> 03:40.742
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

03:40.872 --> 03:43.962
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

03:56.236 --> 03:58.760
-[SIRENS BLARING]

04:02.111 --> 04:03.286
-J.D.: WHAT'S WITH
THE BLUE UNIFORMS

04:03.417 --> 04:05.288
AND WHAT THE
HECK IS BAYGUARD?

04:06.246 --> 04:07.595
-MITCH: YOU
DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

04:07.725 --> 04:08.639
-J.D.: YEAH, I DO.

04:08.770 --> 04:10.989
-[COUGHING]

04:12.208 --> 04:13.383
-WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

04:13.514 --> 04:15.167
-THAT'S THE SECOND
TIME THIS WEEK.

04:15.298 --> 04:16.908
-LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE TAKING
OVER THE SAND AND SEA TOO.

04:17.648 --> 04:19.868
-COULD SOMEBODY FILL ME
IN ON WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:19.998 --> 04:21.303
WHO ARE THESE GUYS?

04:23.306 --> 04:25.090
-ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,
EXCUSE ME. BREAK IT UP.

04:25.221 --> 04:26.875
PARTY'S OVER. EXCUSE ME.

04:27.005 --> 04:29.834
CAN WE GET A LITTLE
CROWD CONTROL HERE?

04:31.053 --> 04:32.315
-THAT'S MITCH BUCHANNON.

04:32.446 --> 04:34.274
[MUMBLED WHISPERING]

04:41.977 --> 04:45.415
-ALEXIS RYKER, CAPTAIN,
BAYGUARD LIFESAVING SERVICES.

04:45.546 --> 04:46.938
MY FRIENDS CALL ME ALEX.

04:47.765 --> 04:51.116
I FINALLY GET TO MEET THE
LEGENDARY MITCH BUCHANNON.

04:51.900 --> 04:53.467
-LEGENDARY ACCORDING TO WHO?

04:53.597 --> 04:55.556
-ACCORDING TO THE BACKGROUND
CHECK I RAN ON YOU.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.122
-BACKGROUND CHECK?

04:57.253 --> 04:58.428
-YEAH, GOT A COPY OF
IT BACK AT THE OFFICE

04:58.559 --> 04:59.647
IF YOU'D LIKE TO SEE IT.

05:00.474 --> 05:02.302
-NO, AT FIRST I'D
LIKE TO SEE THE PERMIT

05:02.432 --> 05:03.912
FOR THE PARASAILOR.

05:04.042 --> 05:05.653
-ACTUALLY, THAT'S BACK
AT THE OFFICE AS WELL.

05:05.783 --> 05:08.090
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT, YOU
ARE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

05:08.220 --> 05:10.527
IT IS WAY TOO DANGEROUS
OUT HERE FOR PARASAILING.

05:11.223 --> 05:13.748
ERNIE, COULD YOU TELL MR.
COLE WE'RE SHUTTING DOWN

05:13.878 --> 05:15.140
THE PARASAILING CONCESSION?

05:15.271 --> 05:16.316
-ERNIE: GOT IT.
-THANKS.

05:17.926 --> 05:19.188
WHY DON'T I SHOW YOU AROUND?

05:19.319 --> 05:20.581
YOU MAY LEARN A FEW THINGS.

05:25.890 --> 05:27.544
THEN, WE PICKED UP THE LEASE

05:27.675 --> 05:29.154
ON YOUR OLD
COUNTY HEADQUARTERS.

05:29.285 --> 05:31.200
NOW TELL ME, WHY WOULD
YOU EVER GIVE THAT UP?

05:31.331 --> 05:33.768
-WE LOST IT IN THE LAST
ROUND OF LOCAL BUDGET CUTS.

05:33.898 --> 05:35.030
-AH-HA.

05:35.770 --> 05:37.467
-YOU SURE ARE PUTTING A LOT
OF MONEY INTO THIS PLACE.

05:37.598 --> 05:39.861
-YUP AND WITH THE
ADDITION OF SAND AND SEA,

05:39.991 --> 05:43.255
BAYGUARD NOW HAS CONTRACTS
WITH EVERY PRIVATE CLUB

05:43.386 --> 05:45.780
FROM PALACE VERDAIS TO
THE VENTURA COUNTY LINE.

05:45.910 --> 05:48.522
-PRIVATE BEACHES ONLY MAKE
UP 10% OF THE COAST LINE.

05:49.610 --> 05:51.655
-8% BUT WHO'S COUNTING?

05:51.786 --> 05:54.136
-SO, WHY ARE YOU GOING AFTER
ALL MY PEOPLE TO WORK FOR YOU?

05:54.919 --> 05:56.965
-IS THAT THE BUZZ
AROUND HEADQUARTERS?

05:57.095 --> 05:58.749
-THAT'S THE BUZZ, BUT
THAT'S NOT THE ANSWER

05:58.880 --> 05:59.707
TO THE QUESTION.

06:01.012 --> 06:03.624
-WELL, YOU MAY NOT
BE AWARE OF THIS,

06:03.754 --> 06:06.496
BUT NEXT FRIDAY BAYWATCH'S
CONTRACT WITH THE COUNTY

06:06.627 --> 06:07.845
IS GOING TO EXPIRE.

06:10.326 --> 06:12.197
-YOU'RE GOING
AFTER OUR CONTRACT?

06:12.981 --> 06:14.765
-IT'S CALLED PRIVATIZATION.

06:14.896 --> 06:17.115
IT IS THE LATEST TREND
IN PUBLIC SERVICE.

06:17.246 --> 06:19.857
IT'S HAPPENING IN HEALTHCARE,
EDUCATION, YOU NAME IT.

06:20.728 --> 06:24.253
NOW IF WE CAN PROVIDE THE
COUNTY WITH A MORE EFFICIENT

06:24.384 --> 06:26.908
SERVICE FOR LESS MONEY,
WELL, THEN WHY NOT?

06:27.604 --> 06:28.605
-YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS.

06:28.736 --> 06:30.085
-OH, I'M VERY SERIOUS.

06:30.215 --> 06:32.566
ACTUALLY, I'M SURPRISED
BY YOUR REACTION.

06:32.696 --> 06:34.742
I MEAN, I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT BE UP

06:34.872 --> 06:36.526
FOR A LITTLE
HEALTHY COMPETITION.

06:41.966 --> 06:47.319
-[LIVELY MUSIC]

06:54.457 --> 06:56.720
-♪ I'M THE ONE YOU'RE LOOKING FOR

07:11.474 --> 07:15.565
♪ ITS TEMPTING TO LOOK SKIN DEEP

07:18.612 --> 07:22.572
♪ THE BEAUTY IN SOULS WILL KEEP

07:25.488 --> 07:29.579
♪ THAT'S WHAT THE WORLD WOULD SAY

07:32.539 --> 07:36.194
♪ DARE YOU TO WALK AWAY

07:38.806 --> 07:43.593
♪ WHEN IT SEEMS THAT ALL
YOUR DREAMS ARE SCARS ♪

07:46.466 --> 07:50.992
♪ I BELIEVE THAT LOVE
CAN CHANGE THE HEART ♪

07:51.122 --> 07:54.169
♪ MAYBE I'M THE ONE YOU'RE LOOKING FOR

07:55.039 --> 07:58.303
♪ WHOA WHOA

08:02.046 --> 08:05.441
♪ WHOA WHOA

08:08.792 --> 08:12.796
♪ SOME THINGS ARE MEANT TO BE

08:15.973 --> 08:19.542
♪ EVEN WHEN YOU CAN'T SEE

08:23.154 --> 08:26.549
♪ A PROMISE YOU'LL MAKE IT THROUGH

08:26.680 --> 08:29.204
♪ A PROMISE YOU'LL MAKE IT THROUGH

08:30.248 --> 08:33.774
♪ WATCHING IT ALL COME TRUE

08:36.558 --> 08:41.042
♪ WHEN IT SEEMS THAT ALL
YOUR DREAMS ARE SCARS ♪

08:43.784 --> 08:48.049
♪ I BELIEVE THAT LOVE
CAN CHANGE THE HEART ♪

08:48.615 --> 08:51.443
♪ MAYBE I'M THE ONE YOU'RE LOOKING FOR ♪

08:52.270 --> 08:55.099
♪ WHOA WHOA

08:56.666 --> 08:58.189
-OH, LET ME ASK HER.

09:00.235 --> 09:05.283
-[SPEAKING PORTUGUESE]

09:08.112 --> 09:10.680
-EXCUSE ME, SIR.

09:11.507 --> 09:14.031
EXCUSE ME. HELLO?

09:17.034 --> 09:19.559
EXCUSE ME! CAN I HELP YOU?

09:19.689 --> 09:22.300
-POR FAVOR! I MUST
FOCUS HERE ON MY WORK.

09:22.431 --> 09:25.652
-NO, YOU CAN'T JUST,
YOU CAN'T STAND HERE.

09:25.782 --> 09:27.175
-PLEASE FORGIVE MY MANNERS.

09:27.305 --> 09:30.700
I WAS JUST ENTHRALLED
BY YOUR EXQUISITE,

09:30.831 --> 09:32.223
HOW DO I SAY THAT?

09:32.354 --> 09:33.616
WOW.

09:33.747 --> 09:35.270
-I GET THE PICTURE.

09:35.400 --> 09:36.401
-[SPEAKS PORTUGUESE]

09:37.881 --> 09:39.579
-LOOK, IT'S NOT JUST ME.

09:39.709 --> 09:41.668
YOU'VE BEEN LEERING AT EVERY
GIRL ON THIS ENTIRE BEACH.

09:41.798 --> 09:43.800
-PLEASE LOOK, THIS WILL
EXPLAIN EVERYTHING.

09:43.931 --> 09:45.672
[SPEAKS PORTUGUESE]

09:45.802 --> 09:48.500
I HOPE TO SEE YOU SOON. WOW.

09:48.631 --> 09:50.067
PERFECT FEET.

09:53.114 --> 09:56.160
-OKAY, MOVE
ALONG. THANK YOU.

09:56.291 --> 09:57.597
-CIAO.

09:57.727 --> 09:58.815
-BRIDGET: HAVE A GOOD DAY.
-YOU, TOO.

09:58.946 --> 09:59.686
-BRIDGET: BYE.
-TAKE CARE.

09:59.816 --> 10:00.600
-BRIDGET: BYE-BYE.

10:10.305 --> 10:11.567
-[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

10:11.698 --> 10:13.047
-HEY, CHIEF, YOU BUSY?

10:13.177 --> 10:16.180
-MITCH, WE WERE JUST
TALKING ABOUT YOU.

10:18.052 --> 10:20.576
-HI, MITCH.
-MITCH: HI.

10:21.533 --> 10:23.100
AM I INTERRUPTING?

10:23.231 --> 10:26.234
-NO, NOT AT ALL. ACTUALLY
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

10:26.364 --> 10:29.063
-YES, ALEX, HAS QUITE AN
INTERESTING PRESENTATION.

10:29.193 --> 10:30.978
-REALLY, I BET SHE DOES.

10:32.066 --> 10:34.416
-SHE WAS JUST SHOWING ME A
TAPE OF SOME OF HER RESCUES.

10:34.546 --> 10:36.200
-REALLY? BAYGUARD'S
GREATEST HITS?

10:36.331 --> 10:38.638
-IT'S QUITE IMPRESSIVE.

10:43.338 --> 10:45.906
-WE VIDEOTAPE OUR
COMPANY PERSONNEL ON A DAILY BASIS.

10:46.036 --> 10:48.909
THAT WAY WE CAN SHOW OUR
CLIENTS THE QUALITY OF WORK

10:49.039 --> 10:51.433
AND QUITE FRANKLY IT KEEPS
THE LIFEGUARDS ON THEIR TOES.

10:51.563 --> 10:53.957
-THEY KNOW THEY'RE BEING
VIDEOTAPED OBVIOUSLY

10:54.088 --> 10:56.090
THEY'RE GOING TO
BE ON THEIR TOES.

10:56.220 --> 10:57.918
-AND THE PROBLEM
WITH THAT IS?

10:58.048 --> 10:59.876
-YOU SAID YOU
HAD ANOTHER TAPE?

11:00.007 --> 11:02.749
-YES, ACTUALLY THIS ONE HAS A
DIFFERENT CAST OF CHARACTERS.

11:02.879 --> 11:05.229
THOUGH I'M SURE THEY'LL
BE FAMILIAR TO YOU.

11:07.797 --> 11:10.191
THIS WAS TAKEN DURING A
RECENT EIGHT HOUR SHIFT.

11:11.932 --> 11:14.151
LET'S START WITH JACK DARIUS.

11:14.282 --> 11:16.763
HE'S LINING UP A DATE
FOR SATURDAY NIGHT.

11:17.502 --> 11:20.114
THAT'S CODY MADISON
AT MOCK TWO SPEED.

11:20.244 --> 11:21.768
MUST BE ON
HIS LUNCH BREAK.

11:21.898 --> 11:25.119
APRIL GIMINSKI WITH
HER BACK TO THE WATER.

11:30.080 --> 11:31.952
-I THINK I SEE
WHERE THIS IS GOING.

11:33.344 --> 11:36.652
-ALEX: CODY AGAIN. I WONDER
WHAT HE'S TALKING ABOUT.

11:39.220 --> 11:40.569
THAT'S THE MIDDLE
OF THE AFTERNOON

11:40.700 --> 11:42.745
AND I BELIEVE
NEWMAN'S WORKING OUT.

11:44.181 --> 11:46.401
WHAT IS SHE DOING
BEHIND THOSE BOARDS?

11:46.531 --> 11:48.620
I WONDER IF SHE CAN
SEE FROM THAT ANGLE.

11:49.839 --> 11:52.668
TWO HOURS LATER AND
NEWMAN'S STILL WORKING OUT?

11:52.799 --> 11:54.235
-MITCH: HOLD ON A MINUTE.

11:54.365 --> 11:57.281
-ALEX: WAIT, WAIT, WAIT!
AND HERE WE HAVE CODY

11:57.412 --> 11:58.718
STILL ON THE PHONE.

12:00.067 --> 12:02.678
J.D. COMING OUT
OF HIBERNATION.

12:06.029 --> 12:07.727
-WHAT IS THIS?
A SMEAR CAMPAIGN?

12:07.857 --> 12:10.164
-IT IS MERELY A RANDOM SAMPLING
OF WHAT GOES ON OUT THERE.

12:10.294 --> 12:12.340
-TAKEN TOTALLY
OUT OF CONTEXT.

12:12.470 --> 12:14.777
-I DIDN'T SAY THERE WAS
ANYTHING SCIENTIFIC ABOUT IT.

12:15.386 --> 12:18.868
ALL I'M SAYING IS THAT THE
PUBLIC DESERVES THE BENEFITS

12:18.999 --> 12:20.609
OF OPEN COMPETITION.

12:20.740 --> 12:22.611
IF THE POWER'S THAT BE
THINK THAT YOU'RE THE BETTER

12:22.742 --> 12:24.047
MAN FOR THE
JOB, THAT'S FINE.

12:24.178 --> 12:26.397
I WOULD JUST LIKE
TO PRESENT OUR CASE.

12:28.269 --> 12:29.879
-I'LL SET UP A MEETING WITH
THE COUNTY COMMISSIONERS.

12:30.010 --> 12:31.054
-ALEX: THANK YOU.

12:31.185 --> 12:32.882
-BASED ON WHAT?
A VIDEOTAPE.

12:33.013 --> 12:34.928
-BASED ON THE FACT THAT IT'S
ULTIMATELY THEIR DECISION.

12:36.494 --> 12:37.757
-I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

12:37.887 --> 12:39.149
-DON'T TAKE IT
PERSONALLY, MITCH.

12:39.280 --> 12:40.629
LIFEGUARDING HAS
BECOME A BUSINESS

12:40.760 --> 12:43.023
JUST LIKE ANY
OTHER BUSINESS.

12:43.153 --> 12:45.242
HERE YOU ARE,
CHIEF, THANK YOU.

12:47.897 --> 12:49.246
WELCOME TO THE 90S.

13:01.171 --> 13:03.260
-I HEARD SHE'S OFFERED
EVERYBODY A JOB.

13:03.391 --> 13:05.349
-WORD IS SHE'S GOING TO
TAKE UP THE ENTIRE BEACH.

13:05.480 --> 13:06.829
-HI, MITCH.
-MITCH: GOOD MORNING.

13:08.613 --> 13:10.137
-SHE USED TO BE AN
ORANGE COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

13:10.267 --> 13:12.269
-IN THE LOUNGE,
PLEASE. IN THE LOUNGE.

13:16.099 --> 13:17.666
MEETING IN THE LOUNGE, BOYS!

13:18.449 --> 13:20.582
JOE, CHRIS, IN THE
LOUNGE. EVERYBODY!

13:20.712 --> 13:22.889
-IT'S LIKE THE
TYSON HOYFIELD FIGHT.

13:23.019 --> 13:24.847
YOU KNOW WHEN
TYSON BIT HIS EAR?

13:24.978 --> 13:26.109
-REAL BABE.

13:28.329 --> 13:29.460
-ALL RIGHT.

13:31.941 --> 13:34.030
I'M SURE YOU ALL HEARD
THE RUMORS, RIGHT?

13:34.161 --> 13:37.468
SOME OF YOU MAY HAVE EVEN
BEEN OFFERED JOBS BY NOW.

13:38.339 --> 13:39.906
HERE'S WHAT'S GOING ON.

13:40.036 --> 13:43.823
THE COUNTY IS CONSIDERING
BAYGUARD'S PROPOSAL.

13:43.953 --> 13:46.521
TO ACHIEVE THAT END, THEY
MADE A LITTLE MUSICAL VIDEO

13:46.651 --> 13:51.352
OF ALL OF YOU MINUS THE MUSIC
AND MINUS YOUR PERMISSION.

13:52.440 --> 13:55.573
WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO SEE IS
NOT FOR THE FAINT OF HEART.

13:55.704 --> 14:00.752
OKAY, WHO CAN TELL ME WHAT'S
WRONG WITH THIS PICTURE?

14:03.407 --> 14:07.020
-COME ON, MITCH. SHE'S ASKING
DIRECTIONS FOR THE BATHROOM.

14:07.150 --> 14:08.935
-IT DOESN'T MATTER.
IT'S THE IMAGE.

14:09.065 --> 14:11.067
PEOPLE ALREADY THINK ALL
LIFEGUARDS DO IS TALK

14:11.198 --> 14:12.503
TO PRETTY GIRLS.

14:13.113 --> 14:14.331
WHAT ABOUT THIS?

14:15.811 --> 14:17.465
WHAT'S THE SPEED
LIMIT ON THE BEACH?

14:18.379 --> 14:20.903
-THE BEACH WAS EMPTY, MITCH.
DO YOU SEE ANYONE AROUND?

14:21.034 --> 14:22.905
-FOUR MILES AN HOUR,
PAL, AT ALL TIMES.

14:23.036 --> 14:24.254
FOUR MILES AN HOUR.

14:24.385 --> 14:25.777
WHAT ABOUT THIS?

14:28.432 --> 14:31.348
WHAT IS THE CARDINAL
RULE OF LIFEGUARDING?

14:31.479 --> 14:34.351
THE NUMBER ONE PRIORITY
ABOVE ALL ELSE?

14:34.482 --> 14:36.876
-ALL: WATCH YOUR WATER.
-HELLO?

14:37.006 --> 14:38.181
-THERE WAS A FIGHT
IN THE PARKING LOT.

14:38.312 --> 14:39.791
-IT DOESN'T MATTER.
YOU CALL IT IN.

14:39.922 --> 14:40.967
YOU LET THE
POLICE HANDLE IT.

14:41.097 --> 14:42.316
-WHAT ABOUT THIS?

14:43.404 --> 14:45.754
I'M SURE THAT WAS
NOT A PERSONAL CALL.

14:46.363 --> 14:48.844
-IT WASN'T. IT WASN'T, MAN.

14:48.975 --> 14:50.672
-[LAUGHING]

14:50.802 --> 14:52.717
-THERE'S SOMETHING
SOMEONE DID RIGHT.

14:55.503 --> 14:57.505
BRIDGET, BRIDGET, BRIDGET.

14:57.635 --> 15:00.073
YOU NEVER LET ANYTHING
BLOCK YOUR VIEW.

15:02.858 --> 15:05.121
NO MORE WORK OUTS IN
THE MIDDLE OF THE DAY.

15:06.253 --> 15:07.994
ONCE AGAIN ON THE PHONE.

15:08.124 --> 15:10.779
-MITCH, I WAS TELLING J.D.
ABOUT A VERY SERIOUS RIP.

15:10.910 --> 15:11.867
READ MY LIPS!

15:11.998 --> 15:12.868
-REALLY?

15:13.651 --> 15:16.306
AT WHICH POINT HE
SPRINGS INTO ACTION.

15:16.437 --> 15:18.091
-[LAUGHING]

15:18.221 --> 15:19.657
-WELL, IT'S NOT THAT FUNNY.

15:20.397 --> 15:22.791
I HOPE YOU ALL REALIZE
WHAT'S AT STAKE HERE.

15:22.922 --> 15:25.533
WE DON'T GET OUR ACT
TOGETHER BY FRIDAY,

15:26.186 --> 15:28.144
WE'RE ALL OUT OF A JOB.

15:31.452 --> 15:37.458
-[GROUP MURMURING]

15:49.122 --> 15:51.167
-ALEX: SO, I FINALLY
GET TO MEET THE LEGENDARY

15:51.298 --> 15:52.603
MITCH BUCHANNON.

15:52.734 --> 15:54.344
-MITCH: LEGENDARY
ACCORDING TO WHO?

15:54.475 --> 15:56.564
-ACCORDING TO THE BACKGROUND
CHECK I RAN ON YOU.

15:56.694 --> 15:58.087
-MITCH: BACKGROUND CHECK?

15:58.218 --> 15:59.567
-YEAH, GOT A COPY OF
IT BACK AT THE OFFICE

15:59.697 --> 16:01.308
IF YOU'D LIKE TO SEE IT.

16:01.438 --> 16:05.573
WELL, YOU MAY NOT BE AWARE
OF THIS, BUT NEXT FRIDAY,

16:05.703 --> 16:09.664
THE BAYWATCH CONTRACT
WITH THE COUNTY EXPIRES.

16:10.447 --> 16:13.798
ALEXIS RYKER, LIEUTENANT,
BAYGUARD LIFESAVING SERVICES.

16:13.929 --> 16:15.583
MY FRIENDS CALL ME ALEX.

16:28.509 --> 16:30.946
GOT A COPY OF IT BACK AT THE
OFFICE IF YOU'D LIKE TO SEE IT.

16:31.077 --> 16:33.905
-NO, FIRST I'D LIKE TO SEE
THE PERMIT FOR THE PARASAILOR.

16:35.342 --> 16:37.170
YOU'RE GOING AFTER
OUR CONTRACT?

16:37.866 --> 16:39.172
YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS.

17:06.763 --> 17:09.419
-IF IT ISN'T MR.
BAYWATCH HIMSELF.

17:09.984 --> 17:11.421
-HELLO, RYKER.

17:12.596 --> 17:15.121
-LIKE THEY SAY, YOU CAN RUN
BUT YOU SURE CAN'T HIDE.

17:15.251 --> 17:17.862
-[CHUCKLING]

17:20.300 --> 17:22.563
-SEE YOU KEEP YOURSELF
IN GOOD SHAPE.

17:24.042 --> 17:25.695
FOR A MAN YOUR AGE.

17:27.175 --> 17:29.570
-ALL RIGHT, DO
ME A FAVOR.

17:29.700 --> 17:31.441
LET'S NOT MAKE
THIS PERSONAL.

17:31.572 --> 17:33.617
-WELL, I THINK IT'S ALREADY
GOTTEN PERSONAL, DON'T YOU?

17:33.748 --> 17:35.228
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

17:35.358 --> 17:37.665
WHY DON'T WE DO OUR BEST
TO TRY AND CHANGE THAT.

17:37.795 --> 17:40.189
-WELL, I THINK IT'S ACTUALLY
A LITTLE TOO LATE FOR THAT.

17:40.320 --> 17:42.583
SEE, I'VE BEEN WONDERING
IF THIS BEACH IS BIG ENOUGH

17:42.713 --> 17:44.193
FOR THE BOTH OF US.

17:44.324 --> 17:45.890
FORTUNATELY, WE WON'T
HAVE TO WAIT TOO LONG

17:46.021 --> 17:47.414
TO FIND THAT OUT,
NOW WILL WE?

17:50.591 --> 17:52.071
YOU HAVE A GOOD
DAY, BUCHANNON.

17:52.810 --> 17:53.985
-YOU, TOO.

17:55.335 --> 17:56.423
RYKER.

18:36.854 --> 18:41.903
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:11.802 --> 19:12.760
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:12.890 --> 19:14.544
-THIS IS BAYGUARD WATER.

19:14.675 --> 19:16.590
-YEAH, WELL THAT MAN
NEEDS HELP. NOW LET ME GO.

19:16.720 --> 19:18.200
-WE GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

19:18.331 --> 19:19.201
-GIVE ME THE CAN.
-WE GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

19:19.332 --> 19:20.463
-EXCUSE ME, HEY, HEY.

19:20.594 --> 19:22.204
IS THERE A PROBLEM HERE?

19:22.335 --> 19:24.598
-YES, THERE'S A PROBLEM.
THIS MAN ALMOST BROKE MY NECK.

19:24.728 --> 19:26.948
-WELL, OBVIOUSLY WE
HAVE IT UNDER CONTROL.

19:28.123 --> 19:29.690
-YOU HAVE A BIG PROBLEM.

19:29.820 --> 19:31.387
-YOU'RE THE ONE
WITH THE PROBLEM.

19:31.518 --> 19:33.520
NEXT TIME DON'T LET YOUR
CAN DRAG IN THE SAND.

19:33.650 --> 19:36.087
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
COME ON. THAT'S IT.

19:36.218 --> 19:38.002
LET'S GO, ARNOLD, COME ON.

19:50.841 --> 19:52.278
-HEY, APRIL.

19:52.408 --> 19:53.540
-APRIL: HEY, BRIDGET.

19:54.193 --> 19:55.585
-YOU'RE INTO
FASHION, RIGHT?

19:56.369 --> 19:58.414
YOU EVER HEARD
THIS GUY TAMALE?

20:00.242 --> 20:01.243
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

20:02.897 --> 20:04.115
PAOLO TAMALE?

20:04.246 --> 20:05.029
-MM-HM.

20:05.160 --> 20:06.640
-OF COURSE.

20:06.770 --> 20:08.511
YOU MEAN YOU'VE NEVER
HEARD OF HOT TAMALES?

20:09.251 --> 20:11.384
HE'S THE MOST FAMOUS SWIMWEAR
DESIGNER IN THE WORLD.

20:11.514 --> 20:13.255
-NO WAY, NOT THIS GUY.

20:13.386 --> 20:14.865
-I'VE HEARD HE'S A
LITTLE WEIRD, BUT I MEAN,

20:14.996 --> 20:16.345
HE'S FROM BRAZIL,
SO WHO KNOWS?

20:16.476 --> 20:18.173
WHERE'D YOU GET THIS?

20:18.304 --> 20:19.914
-HE GAVE IT TO ME. SAID HE
WAS LOOKING FOR SOME MODELS.

20:20.044 --> 20:21.568
-WELL, WHEN? WHERE?

20:21.698 --> 20:23.439
-BRIDGET: IT SHOULD
SAY ON THE CARD.

20:24.397 --> 20:25.789
-WELL, YOU'RE GONNA
DO IT, AREN'T YA?

20:27.748 --> 20:29.184
-I COULD USE THE
EXTRA MONEY.

20:30.577 --> 20:31.969
-I COULD USE THE EXPOSURE.

20:33.841 --> 20:35.364
YOU'RE WHAT
ABOUT A SIZE SIX?

20:37.714 --> 20:40.761
-EXCUSE ME. APRIL, MITCH
NEEDS TO SEE YOU RIGHT AWAY.

20:41.936 --> 20:43.198
-OKAY, HERE YOU GO.

20:54.775 --> 20:56.951
-MITCH: APRIL, I MADE AN
APPOINTMENT FOR US TO SEE RYKER

20:57.081 --> 20:58.431
AT BAYGUARD HEADQUARTERS.

20:59.258 --> 21:01.085
-WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA SAY TO HER?

21:01.216 --> 21:03.262
-WE'RE GONNA MAKE THE
POINT THAT WE RESPOND

21:03.392 --> 21:05.133
TO ALL CALLS.

21:05.264 --> 21:07.657
THERE ARE NO SUCH THINGS AS
PROPERTY LINES IN THE OCEAN.

21:08.963 --> 21:10.225
THEY OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.

21:25.414 --> 21:27.068
-MITCH, THAT'S THE
GUY WHO STOPPED ME.

21:29.897 --> 21:31.246
-ARNOLD: HERE'S
FOR A JOB WELL DONE.

21:31.377 --> 21:32.639
-MAN: COOL, THAT'S
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

21:32.769 --> 21:33.553
-ARNOLD: DON'T
WORRY, IT'S ALL THERE.

21:33.683 --> 21:36.469
-YEAH, SEE YA, BROTHER.

21:37.644 --> 21:38.601
-LATER.

21:51.266 --> 21:52.659
-HEY.
-CODY: WHAT'S UP, MAN?

21:54.574 --> 21:55.662
MORE HOME VIDEOS.

21:55.792 --> 21:57.054
WHAT'D THEY GET ON US NOW?

22:02.930 --> 22:04.105
WHY'D YOU FREEZE FRAME?

22:04.235 --> 22:06.542
-I JUST SAW THAT
GUY TAKE A PAY OFF

22:06.673 --> 22:08.414
OUTSIDE BAYGUARD HEADQUARTERS.

22:09.371 --> 22:11.460
THAT WHOLE THING
WAS A SET UP, PAL.

22:11.591 --> 22:13.288
THAT RESCUE WAS STAGED.

22:20.774 --> 22:22.906
-BRIDGET: APRIL, I DON'T
THINK THIS IS SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

22:23.429 --> 22:25.256
-IT'S OKAY, BRIDGET.

22:25.387 --> 22:27.998
EVERY SHIFT WE GET AN HOUR FOR
WORK OUT. YOU'RE WORKING OUT.

22:28.564 --> 22:30.218
-BRIDGET: IF MITCH SEES US.

22:31.132 --> 22:32.307
-HE WON'T.

22:33.177 --> 22:35.049
-BRIDGET: WITH ALL THIS
VIDEOTAPING GOING ON,

22:35.179 --> 22:37.312
IF WE GET CAUGHT,
WE'RE DEAD.

22:37.443 --> 22:39.706
-WILL YOU STOP WORRYING?
NOW HOW DOES IT FIT?

22:40.533 --> 22:42.273
-OKAY. IS THIS ALL OF IT?

22:42.404 --> 22:44.319
-YES, NOW LET ME SEE.

22:47.366 --> 22:48.628
-WHAT DO YOU THINK?

22:55.678 --> 22:57.158
-I THINK YOU'LL
GET HIS ATTENTION.

22:57.767 --> 22:59.552
AND WHEN YOU DO, YOU HAVE
TO BE SURE TO MENTION

22:59.682 --> 23:01.989
THAT IT'S AN APRIL G.
ORIGINAL AT WHICH POINT

23:02.119 --> 23:03.991
I'LL HAND HIM MY PORTFOLIO,
HE'LL LOVE MY STUFF

23:04.121 --> 23:05.166
AND WE'LL BECOME
RICH AND FAMOUS.

23:05.296 --> 23:07.647
-OKAY, CAN I
CHANGE BACK NOW?

23:07.777 --> 23:10.214
-NO, I NEED YOU TRY
ON ONE MORE SUIT.

23:10.345 --> 23:11.346
-I'M GONNA CHANGE BACK NOW.

23:11.477 --> 23:12.869
-ONE MORE.
-BRIDGET: APRIL.

23:13.522 --> 23:15.002
OKAY.

23:28.537 --> 23:31.584
-HEY, MAN. YOU
SURE THAT'S LEGAL?

23:31.714 --> 23:33.194
-JUST FOLLOWING ORDERS.

23:33.324 --> 23:36.589
-YEAH, YOU GUYS REALLY
THINK YOU'RE GONNA GET

23:36.719 --> 23:37.720
THAT COUNTY CONTRACT?

23:37.851 --> 23:39.287
-THAT'S WHAT I HEAR.

23:39.418 --> 23:40.984
-YOUR CAPTAIN
SEEMS PRETTY COOL.

23:41.115 --> 23:42.508
HOW DO YOU LIKE
WORKING FOR HER?

23:42.638 --> 23:43.900
-SHE'S A LITTLE TOO
CORPORATE FOR MY TASTES,

23:44.031 --> 23:45.380
BUT SHE'S OKAY.

23:45.511 --> 23:47.991
DOES WHATEVER
MANAGEMENT TELLS HER.

23:48.122 --> 23:49.428
-I HEAR YA.

23:50.037 --> 23:53.519
I WAS JUST WONDERING 'CAUSE
IF YOU GUYS GET THAT CONTRACT,

23:53.649 --> 23:55.564
I WANNA BE IN THE RIGHT
PLACE AT THE RIGHT TIME.

23:56.609 --> 23:57.523
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

23:58.437 --> 24:00.090
-WE COULD USE
A GUY LIKE YOU.

24:06.009 --> 24:07.750
-LET YOUR BOSS KNOW
I'M INTERESTED, WILL YA?

24:22.809 --> 24:25.420
-EVERY TIME I CALL YOUR
TOWER, YOUR LINE IS BUSY.

24:25.551 --> 24:28.510
HOW MANY TIMES DO I HAVE TO
TELL YOU NO PERSONAL CALLS

24:28.641 --> 24:30.338
WHILE YOU'RE ON DUTY.

24:30.469 --> 24:32.209
-WOULD YOU STOP TREATING ME
LIKE I'M SOME DAMN ROOKIE?

24:32.340 --> 24:34.211
-MITCH: STOP ACTING LIKE ONE!
YOU'RE A VETERAN LIFEGUARD!

24:34.342 --> 24:35.691
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO
SET AN EXAMPLE HERE!

24:35.822 --> 24:36.823
-GIVE ME A BREAK.
YOU KNOW, I'VE HAD IT!

24:36.953 --> 24:38.477
-WELL, I'VE HAD IT WITH YOU!

24:38.607 --> 24:39.869
YOU'RE WALKING ON THIN ICE
WITH ME, PAL, THIN ICE!

24:40.000 --> 24:41.523
-OH,REALLY?
-MITCH: YEAH!

24:41.654 --> 24:42.785
-WELL, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO FIND SOMEONE ELSE

24:42.916 --> 24:43.960
TO KICK AROUND
'CAUSE I QUIT!

24:56.843 --> 24:57.887
-MITCH: YOU HAD IT, MAN.

24:58.018 --> 24:58.975
-HERE! TAKE IT!

24:59.106 --> 25:00.324
IT'S ALL YOURS!

