27:01.663 --> 27:03.534
-ALEX: THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR JOINING ME TODAY.

27:04.274 --> 27:07.408
NOW BAYGUARD IS THE BRAIN
CHILD OF VICTOR COLE.

27:07.538 --> 27:09.802
HE'S A FORMER BALBOA
ISLAND LIFEGUARD

27:09.932 --> 27:11.630
WHO FORMED THE COMPANY
FIVE YEARS AGO.

27:11.760 --> 27:14.720
UNDER HIS DIRECTION, WE
HAVE PULLED RESOURCES

27:14.850 --> 27:18.985
WITH 12 PRIVATE CLUBS,
PERFORM ONE HIGHLY EFFICIENT,

27:19.115 --> 27:21.074
HIGHLY MOBILE RESCUE FORCE.

27:22.684 --> 27:25.774
CODY, CODY, COME ON
OVER, COME ON OVER.

27:26.732 --> 27:30.126
CHIEF, YOU MUST
KNOW CODY MADISON.

27:30.257 --> 27:31.562
-CODY.
-CODY: CHIEF.

27:31.693 --> 27:33.652
-CODY RECENTLY LEFT
BAYWATCH TO JOIN

27:33.782 --> 27:35.479
US HERE AS LIEUTENANT.

27:35.610 --> 27:38.439
-OH, REALLY? I DIDN'T GET
A COPY OF YOUR RESIGNATION.

27:39.222 --> 27:40.223
-MITCH HAS IT.

27:40.833 --> 27:42.486
-ACTUALLY HE'S JUST
ONE OF WHAT WE HOPE

27:42.617 --> 27:45.098
WILL BE MANY BAYWATCH
LIFEGUARDS TO JOIN OUR RANKS.

27:46.055 --> 27:48.144
CODY, I WILL SEE YOU AT THE
4 O'CLOCK STAFF MEETING.

27:48.275 --> 27:49.580
-YOU GOT IT.
-ALEX: GREAT.

27:49.711 --> 27:50.625
-CHIEF.

27:51.931 --> 27:54.498
-NOW, CHIEF, I HAVE
A QUESTION FOR YOU

27:54.629 --> 27:55.891
ABOUT YOUR SWIMSUITS.

27:56.022 --> 27:57.632
WHO IS YOUR SPONSOR?
-CHIEF: SPONSOR?

27:57.763 --> 27:59.547
-ALEX: YES, WHO
PROVIDES YOUR SUITS?

27:59.678 --> 28:01.418
-THE TAX PAYERS.

28:02.637 --> 28:04.421
ACTUALLY, I HAVE A
LITTLE SECRET FOR YOU.

28:04.552 --> 28:06.293
IF YOU PUT A COMPANY
LOGO ON THE SUIT,

28:06.423 --> 28:08.121
THEY PAY FOR THEMSELVES.

28:08.251 --> 28:09.862
-CHIEF: I DON'T
THINK WE CAN DO THAT.

28:09.992 --> 28:11.907
-OH, YES, YOU CAN AND
YOUR TRUCKS, I CAN GET FORD

28:12.038 --> 28:13.604
TO DONATE THEM FOR YOU.

28:13.735 --> 28:16.956
THEY JUST BUILT US A
SPECIAL MODEL WITH A TOWER

28:17.086 --> 28:17.870
IN THE BED.

28:18.000 --> 28:19.654
IT IS STATE OF THE ART.

28:19.785 --> 28:21.525
-YOU'RE SAYING WE CAN
GET ALL OF THIS FOR FREE.

28:21.656 --> 28:23.876
-WELL, EVERYBODY IS LOOKING
FOR PRODUCT PLACEMENT

28:24.006 --> 28:25.225
THESE DAYS, RIGHT?

28:25.355 --> 28:26.617
I WANT YOU TO
PICTURE SOMETHING.

28:27.227 --> 28:29.446
BILLBOARDS ON EVERY TOWER.

28:29.577 --> 28:32.362
WE ARE TALKING PRIME
ADVERTISING SPACE.

28:32.885 --> 28:35.365
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW MUCH REVENUE

28:35.496 --> 28:36.366
THAT CAN GENERATE?

28:37.541 --> 28:39.456
I HAPPEN TO HAVE THE
FIGURES FOR YOU RIGHT HERE.

28:40.196 --> 28:41.241
THERE YOU ARE.

28:42.372 --> 28:44.505
I WOULD LIKE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT OUR EMERGENCY TRAINING.

28:44.635 --> 28:45.767
WHY DON'T WE HEAD BACK THIS WAY.

28:45.898 --> 28:46.942
-EXCUSE ME.
-ALEX: EXCUSE ME.

28:48.161 --> 28:49.118
GOOD JOB.

28:51.207 --> 28:53.688
-YEAH, OKAY.

28:53.819 --> 28:55.211
-MITCH: YOU ON THEIR TURF?

28:55.342 --> 28:56.996
-YEAH, I'M AT THEIR
MOBILE TOWER NOW.

28:57.736 --> 28:58.998
I'LL TAKE A QUICK
LOOK INSIDE.

28:59.128 --> 29:00.173
-MITCH: OKAY.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.394
SEE ANYTHING?

29:04.525 --> 29:05.613
-YEAH, THERE'S A COMPUTER.

29:09.486 --> 29:10.792
OKAY, I'M LOGGED ON.

29:15.841 --> 29:17.103
WHOA.

29:17.233 --> 29:18.669
-WHAT'D YOU FIND?

29:18.800 --> 29:20.019
-MOST OF THEIR PEOPLE
ARE ONLY UNDER CONTRACT

29:20.149 --> 29:21.716
TILL THE END OF THE MONTH.

29:21.847 --> 29:23.413
THEN THEY ALL GO BACK TO
THEIR JOBS IN ORANGE COUNTY.

29:24.110 --> 29:26.025
ALL THAT'S LEFT ARE
A BUNCH OF WANNABES.

29:27.504 --> 29:29.811
-NO WONDER SHE'S
RECRUITING SO HARD.

29:29.942 --> 29:31.857
-BY THE MIDDLE OF THE SUMMER,
SHE'LL HAVE A GRAND TOTAL

29:31.987 --> 29:33.902
OF THREE LIFEGUARDS
TRAINED IN OCEAN RESCUE.

29:34.033 --> 29:35.948
REST WILL BARELY KNOW CPR.

29:36.078 --> 29:37.863
-HEY, CODY, CAN YOU GET
THAT OFF THE COMPUTER?

29:37.993 --> 29:39.778
-I DON'T KNOW IF THIS
THING WILL PRINT OUT.

29:46.045 --> 29:47.176
-MITCH: CODY?
CODY, YOU THERE?

29:47.307 --> 29:48.525
-MITCH, KEEP IT DOWN, MAN.

29:48.656 --> 29:49.744
I DON'T WANT TO
GET BUSTED IN HERE.

29:51.093 --> 29:53.182
-TOO LATE, OUT OF THE TRUCK.

29:54.227 --> 29:56.403
-HEY, HEY, HEY, MAN.
BE COOL, BE COOL.

29:57.143 --> 29:58.274
-HEY, HEY.

30:00.711 --> 30:03.802
AND I HAD SUCH
HIGH HOPES FOR YOU.

30:04.890 --> 30:06.456
LET'S GET HIM OUT
OF HERE, YOU GUYS.

30:08.545 --> 30:12.158
-MITCH: CODY, WHAT'S
GOING ON? ARE YOU THERE?

30:17.337 --> 30:18.729
ALL RIGHT, TOWER 17 TODAY.

30:18.860 --> 30:20.383
BE REAL CAREFUL,
THERE'S LOTS OF RIPS

30:20.514 --> 30:21.776
AND THERE ARE A LOT
OF KIDS OUT THERE.

30:21.907 --> 30:22.821
-OKAY.
-ALL RIGHT, HAVE A GOOD ONE.

30:25.606 --> 30:28.652
-SO, WHAT'S NEXT? TAPPING
MY PHONES, READING MY EMAIL?

30:28.783 --> 30:30.959
-DON'T COME ON TO ME
LIKE SOME MODEL CITIZEN.

30:31.090 --> 30:32.439
NOT AFTER THE
STUNT YOU PULLED.

30:32.569 --> 30:33.832
-WHAT STUNT WOULD THAT BE?

30:33.962 --> 30:35.572
-PAYING OFF THE
PARASAILOR TO GO DOWN.

30:35.703 --> 30:37.748
-EXCUSE ME? WHERE
DID THAT COME FROM?

30:37.879 --> 30:41.578
-ALEX, I SAW ONE
OF YOUR LIFEGUARDS
PAYING OFF A STUNTMAN.

30:43.580 --> 30:45.278
-YOU'RE STARTING
TO HALLUCINATE.

30:45.408 --> 30:46.583
-DON'T GIVE ME THAT, LADY.

30:46.714 --> 30:48.455
YOUR WHOLE
OPERATION'S A FRAUD.

30:48.585 --> 30:50.587
YOU'RE STAGING PHONY RESCUES,
YOU HIRED A TEMPORARY STAFF

30:50.718 --> 30:52.589
UNTIL YOU COULD STEAL
AWAY QUALIFIED LIFEGUARDS.

30:52.720 --> 30:54.461
-IT'S NOT ABOUT SAVING
LIVES FOR YOU, IS IT?

30:54.591 --> 30:55.897
IT'S ABOUT THE MONEY.

30:56.028 --> 30:57.507
-EXCUSE ME, BUT DO
YOU HAVE ANY PROOF

30:57.638 --> 30:58.421
OF THESE ALLEGATIONS?

30:58.552 --> 30:59.988
-WHAT IF I DO?

31:00.119 --> 31:02.251
-WELL, I WOULD RESIGN
WITHOUT HESITATION.

31:03.035 --> 31:05.298
BUT UNTIL THEN, I WOULD
APPRECIATE IT IF YOU WOULD JUST

31:05.428 --> 31:08.997
LET US DO OUR JOB, FREE
OF OUTSIDE INTERFERENCE.

31:09.128 --> 31:13.219
-MITCH! WE JUST GO A
REPORT ON A MISSING KID.

31:13.349 --> 31:15.525
HE'S DISAPPEARED
SOMEWHERE BETWEEN TOWER 10

31:15.656 --> 31:17.614
AND THE SAND AND SEA CLUB
AND HIS PARENTS ARE FRANTIC.

31:17.745 --> 31:19.399
-PUT J.D. AND BRIDGET ON IT!

31:19.529 --> 31:21.531
-I CAN'T, WE JUST HAD A RIP
AT SEVEN AND I HAD TO SEND

31:21.662 --> 31:23.882
THEM THERE AND THERE'S
MORE, HE'S A DIABETIC

31:24.012 --> 31:25.927
AND HE NEEDED HIS
INSULIN AN HOUR AGO.

31:26.623 --> 31:27.929
-WE'LL FINISH THIS LATER.

31:28.060 --> 31:29.017
-WE'RE ON IT.

31:29.148 --> 31:35.067
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

31:35.197 --> 31:38.505
-[SIRENS BLARING]

31:38.635 --> 31:41.334
-DISPATCH: CODE THREE,
MALE MISSING BETWEEN TOWER 10

31:41.464 --> 31:42.901
AND SAND AND SEA.

31:44.293 --> 31:46.687
KNOWN DIABETIC. ALL UNITS
RESPOND IMMEDIATELY.

31:52.345 --> 31:54.825
-AND NO ONE ON DUTY HAS
SEEN ANY SIGN OF HIM.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.218
LOOK, HE COULDN'T
HAVE JUST DISAPPEARED.

31:56.349 --> 31:57.698
-BEEN HANGING
BILLBOARDS ALL DAY.

31:57.828 --> 32:00.135
-LOVELY AND YOU'VE
INTERVIEWED EVERY PERSON

32:00.266 --> 32:01.658
ON THE BEACH?

32:01.789 --> 32:03.051
-NOT EVERYONE. WE
JUST TALKED TO PEOPLE

32:03.182 --> 32:04.574
WHO LOOK LIKE THEY MIGHT--

32:04.705 --> 32:06.054
-LOOK, I DON'T CARE
WHAT THEY LOOK LIKE.

32:06.185 --> 32:08.578
IF THEY CAN SEE OUT
HERE, YOU TALK TO THEM.

32:08.709 --> 32:10.319
NOW GO FIND THAT KID.

32:10.450 --> 32:12.060
-TWO PEOPLE SAW HIM
HEADING IN YOUR DIRECTION

32:12.191 --> 32:13.627
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.

32:13.757 --> 32:15.324
YOUR PEOPLE SAW NOTHING?

32:15.455 --> 32:17.152
-WE'RE CONDUCTING A
THOROUGH SEARCH OF THE AREA

32:17.283 --> 32:18.719
AROUND THE CLUB,
WE'LL HANDLE IT.

32:18.849 --> 32:20.982
-THIS ISN'T ABOUT A
LIFEGUARD COMPETITION.

32:21.113 --> 32:22.418
IT'S ABOUT A
LITTLE BOY'S LIFE.

32:30.165 --> 32:31.819
-WE WILL WORK TOGETHER.

32:33.473 --> 32:34.691
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

32:38.695 --> 32:44.092
-[SOLEMN MUSIC]

32:51.099 --> 32:53.014
-EXCUSE ME, WE'RE LOOKING FOR
A LITTLE BOY WHO'S MISSING

32:53.145 --> 32:54.494
IN A YELLOW T-SHIRT,
HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

32:54.624 --> 32:55.974
-NO.
-MITCH: THANKS.

32:56.104 --> 32:57.671
-EXCUSE ME, HAVE
YOU SEEN A LITTLE BOY

32:57.801 --> 32:58.802
ABOUT EIGHT YEARS OLD, HE
HAD A YELLOW T-SHIRT ON?

32:58.933 --> 33:00.065
-NO, I DIDN'T.
-ALEX: NO?

33:00.674 --> 33:02.458
-TERRIFIC, NO
ONE'S SEEN HIM.

33:27.918 --> 33:30.008
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

33:30.791 --> 33:32.967
MY NAME IS MITCH
AND I'M A LIFEGUARD.

33:33.098 --> 33:34.882
WE'RE LOOKING FOR A
LITTLE BOY WHO'S MISSING

33:35.013 --> 33:35.883
AND HE WAS WEARING
A YELLOW T-SHIRT.

33:36.014 --> 33:37.580
HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

33:37.711 --> 33:39.452
-YEAH, I SAW A LITTLE
BOY WITH A YELLOW T-SHIRT.

33:39.582 --> 33:40.714
HE WENT OVER THERE.

33:48.200 --> 33:49.201
-THANKS.

34:03.780 --> 34:05.217
GATE'S SUPPOSED
TO BE LOCKED.

34:05.347 --> 34:09.569
IF HE WENT INSIDE, HE'S
IN FOR SOME SURPRISE.

34:10.960 --> 34:12.224
GO GET BACK UP.

34:12.353 --> 34:13.572
-HEY, WHY SHOULD
I GO GET BACK UP?

34:13.703 --> 34:14.791
-I'VE BEEN HERE
BEFORE, YOU HAVEN'T.

34:14.922 --> 34:15.748
GO GET BACK UP.

34:15.879 --> 34:17.228
-YOU GO GET BACK UP.

34:17.359 --> 34:19.882
-NOW GO GET BACK UP!

34:27.239 --> 34:29.067
-I AM THE BACK UP.

34:35.029 --> 34:36.204
-HELLO?

34:37.292 --> 34:38.511
ANYBODY IN HERE?

34:41.731 --> 34:42.688
-ALEX: HELLO.

34:43.820 --> 34:45.344
-WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN HERE?

34:45.474 --> 34:47.302
-I'M TRYING TO
SAVE A LOST CHILD.

34:47.433 --> 34:49.435
-MITCH: I THOUGHT I TOLD
YOU TO CALL FOR BACK UP.

34:49.565 --> 34:50.827
-YOU WANT ME TO STAY
HOME AND BAKE COOKIES

34:50.958 --> 34:52.264
WHILE YOU HUNT FOR
BEAR, FORGET IT.

34:52.393 --> 34:55.353
-WHAT? NOBODY
KNOWS WE'RE IN HERE.

34:55.484 --> 34:59.271
-YES, SO LET'S GET THE
KID AND GET OUT, OKAY?

35:00.924 --> 35:02.622
-I WOULDN'T GO THAT WAY.

35:02.752 --> 35:03.927
-WHY NOT?

35:04.058 --> 35:06.365
-THERE'S A DROP OFF.

35:10.978 --> 35:13.023
-WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
TELL ME THAT WAS THERE?

35:13.154 --> 35:14.808
-I HAD COOKIES
IN THE OVEN.

35:21.119 --> 35:22.294
-ALEX: HELLO?

35:22.424 --> 35:24.034
-MITCH: HEY,
ANYBODY IN HERE?

35:24.165 --> 35:25.688
-ALEX: CAN YOU HEAR US?

35:25.819 --> 35:27.560
-MITCH: WE'RE LIFEGUARDS.
IS ANYBODY IN HERE?

35:27.690 --> 35:28.996
-ALEX: HELLO?

35:31.259 --> 35:32.869
-MITCH: YOU DON'T
WANT TO GO THERE.

35:33.000 --> 35:34.828
-WHY NOT? ANOTHER DROP OFF?

35:34.958 --> 35:36.482
-NO, NO, NO.

35:39.789 --> 35:40.790
WHIRLPOOL.

35:51.410 --> 35:53.455
-[SCREAMING]

35:57.459 --> 35:58.634
-HELP!

35:58.765 --> 35:59.679
-ALEX: WE'RE HERE
TO HELP YOU.

36:02.769 --> 36:03.944
KEEP YOUR HEAD UP!

36:11.560 --> 36:12.866
-HELP!

36:16.565 --> 36:18.088
HELP!

36:18.219 --> 36:20.090
-ALEX: HANG IN THERE!
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

36:27.315 --> 36:29.012
MITCH: HANG ON! HANG ON!

36:29.143 --> 36:30.188
SWIM TO ME, OKAY?

36:30.318 --> 36:31.319
SWIM TO ME!

36:33.495 --> 36:34.453
HANG ON!

36:35.149 --> 36:37.151
HERE I AM. GRAB MY HAND!

36:39.066 --> 36:41.286
HANG ON, I GOT
YA. HANG ON.

36:49.816 --> 36:52.166
OKAY, I GOT YA. I GOT YA.

36:53.863 --> 36:54.821
I GOT HIM.

36:57.867 --> 36:59.086
HANG ON, ALEX,
DON'T FIGHT IT.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.827
-ALEX: IT'S STARTING
TO PULL ME DOWN.

37:00.957 --> 37:03.090
-DON'T FIGHT IT.
JUST GO WITH IT.

37:03.960 --> 37:07.137
I'LL GET TO YA. GO WITH IT.

37:16.408 --> 37:17.626
GRAB MY ARM!

37:17.757 --> 37:19.802
ALL RIGHT, EASY, ALL RIGHT.

37:19.933 --> 37:21.500
-WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

37:22.501 --> 37:24.285
-WE CALL FOR BACK UP!

37:42.782 --> 37:44.392
-THAT'S ALEX'S JACKET.

37:46.307 --> 37:47.830
NO, NO, NO, YOU
GO FOR BACK UP.

37:49.136 --> 37:50.485
-WAIT, WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?

37:50.616 --> 37:51.834
-TO PULL THE PLUG.

37:58.014 --> 38:00.582
MITCH! YOU DOWN THERE?

38:00.713 --> 38:02.236
-APRIL! YEAH!

38:02.367 --> 38:04.934
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN,
YOU GOT A RESCUE CAN?

38:05.065 --> 38:06.719
-YEAH!

38:06.849 --> 38:09.809
-HANG ON TO THE CAN, THROW
DOWN THE HARNESS, CODE ON.

38:09.939 --> 38:12.942
GET SOME INSULIN AND HOOK
UP THE CAN TO A WENCH.

38:14.553 --> 38:16.337
TURN THIS DAMN THING OFF!

38:16.468 --> 38:18.731
-YEAH! I'LL GET THEM
TO SHUT OFF THE POWER!

38:21.386 --> 38:22.691
-GRAB THE BOY.
-ALEX: OKAY.

38:22.822 --> 38:24.258
-GOT HIM?
-ALEX: GOT HIM.

38:29.394 --> 38:31.221
-ALL RIGHT, LISTEN TO ME.
PUT YOUR ARMS THROUGH HERE.

38:31.352 --> 38:32.397
ARMS THROUGH.

38:33.049 --> 38:36.966
OKAY, ALL RIGHT, ALL
RIGHT. THAT A BOY.

38:37.097 --> 38:38.054
YOU OKAY?
-YEAH.

38:38.185 --> 38:39.578
-ALL RIGHT, HANG ON!

38:41.841 --> 38:43.582
ALL RIGHT, ALL
RIGHT, OKAY.

38:43.712 --> 38:44.539
-HOLD ON.

38:44.670 --> 38:46.367
-I GOT YOU, I GOT YOU.

38:47.455 --> 38:48.674
COME ON!

38:54.636 --> 38:55.768
-WE DID IT.

38:58.205 --> 38:59.424
-WE?

38:59.554 --> 39:01.382
-OH, THAT'S RIGHT,
YOU KNOW WHAT,

39:01.513 --> 39:04.516
YOU DID IT ALL BY YOURSELF,
THE LEGENDARY MITCH BUCHANNON.

39:04.646 --> 39:06.735
I HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

39:06.866 --> 39:09.042
-NO, NO, YOU'RE
RIGHT. [CHUCKLES]

39:09.172 --> 39:11.131
YOU HAD PLENTY
TO DO WITH IT.

39:11.261 --> 39:14.221
-ARE YOU ALWAYS THIS
HOSTILE AFTER A RESCUE?

39:14.917 --> 39:17.442
-WILL YOU HURRY
UP WITH THAT WENCH?

39:24.013 --> 39:26.581
-REALLY SUCH AN OPPORTUNITY.
-BRIDGET: THANK YOU.

39:26.712 --> 39:31.804
-[GROUP TALKING
OVER ONE ANOTHER]

39:32.457 --> 39:33.806
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

39:34.415 --> 39:35.764
YOU GUYS DRIVE SAFE.

39:35.895 --> 39:37.505
-MISS TAMALE, COME ON.

39:37.636 --> 39:39.289
-BYE, THANKS.

39:40.639 --> 39:42.162
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU TURNED HIM DOWN.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.861
-I'M A LIFEGUARD,
NOT A HOT TAMALE.

39:45.992 --> 39:47.907
BESIDES, IT'S WINTER
TIME IN BRAZIL

39:48.037 --> 39:48.908
AND I'M READY FOR SUMMER.

39:49.691 --> 39:51.998
-I DON'T SUPPOSE THAT
PAOLO SAID ANYTHING

39:52.128 --> 39:54.043
ABOUT MY PORTFOLIO.
-AS A MATTER OF FACT--

39:54.174 --> 39:56.219
-HE HATED IT, I KNEW IT.
FORGET IT, I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

39:56.350 --> 39:58.787
-NO, NO, HE SAID YOU WERE
A VERY TALENTED DESIGNER

39:58.918 --> 40:00.659
AND THAT YOU SHOULD
STOP BEING SO INSECURE.

40:00.789 --> 40:01.877
YOUR TIME WILL COME.

40:02.008 --> 40:03.618
-MY TIME WILL COME, HUH?

40:03.749 --> 40:05.272
WERE THOSE HIS EXACT WORDS?

40:05.403 --> 40:08.275
-WELL, ACTUALLY, HIS
ASSISTANT WAS TRANSLATING,

40:08.406 --> 40:10.146
BUT I KNOW THAT'S
WHAT HE MEANT.

40:10.886 --> 40:11.844
HE'S RIGHT, APRIL.

40:11.974 --> 40:13.193
-THANKS, BRIDGET.

40:14.803 --> 40:16.022
-LADIES.
-APRIL: HEY.

40:16.152 --> 40:17.110
-HEY, CHIEF.

40:17.240 --> 40:18.677
-CHIEF: HI, MITCH.

40:18.807 --> 40:19.591
-WHAT HAPPENED TO THE
COUNTY'S COMMISSIONERS?

40:19.721 --> 40:20.679
-THEY COULDN'T MAKE IT.

40:20.809 --> 40:22.245
-HEY, HEY, HANG ON A SECOND.

40:22.376 --> 40:24.204
YOU PROMISED ME THEY
WOULD TOUR MY FACILITY

40:24.334 --> 40:25.553
BEFORE THEY MAKE A DECISION.

40:25.684 --> 40:27.381
-THERE'S NO
DECISION TO MAKE.

40:27.512 --> 40:30.776
BAYGUARD WITHDREW THEIR BID
WHEN ALEX RYKER RESIGNED.

40:31.646 --> 40:33.169
-ALEX RESIGNED.

40:33.300 --> 40:35.258
-I KNOW YOU TWO DIDN'T
ALWAYS SEE EYE TO EYE.

40:35.389 --> 40:36.999
-THAT'S OKAY, I WISH
HER NOTHING BUT THE BEST

40:37.130 --> 40:38.653
DOWN THERE IN ORANGE COUNTY.

40:38.784 --> 40:40.960
-ACTUALLY, THAT'S WHAT I
CAME TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

40:41.090 --> 40:44.006
NOW, THIS IN NO WAY IS
A REFLECTION ON THE JOB
THAT YOU'RE DOING.

40:44.137 --> 40:45.138
I MEAN, THE BEACH
HAS NEVER BEEN SAFER.

40:45.268 --> 40:46.705
-BUT.

40:46.835 --> 40:48.533
-BUT YOU'RE TWO MONTHS
BEHIND ON YOUR PAPERWORK

40:48.663 --> 40:51.057
AND 20% OVER BUDGET
AT LAST COUNT

40:51.187 --> 40:53.712
AND FRANKLY, I DON'T SEE
ANY SIGNS OF IMPROVEMENT.

40:53.842 --> 40:55.409
I MEAN, WE BOTH KNOW THAT
ADMINISTRATION IS NOT

40:55.540 --> 40:57.890
YOUR STRONG SUIT, I MEAN,
YOU'RE A FIELD GENERAL.

40:58.804 --> 41:00.501
-A FIELD GENERAL.

41:00.632 --> 41:02.372
-EXACTLY WHICH IS WHY I'VE
DECIDED TO BRING ALEX IN AS A--

41:02.503 --> 41:03.939
-NO.

41:04.070 --> 41:04.984
-CHIEF: AS AN
ADMINISTRATIVE CONSULTANT--

41:05.114 --> 41:06.115
-DON'T YOU DO THIS TO ME.

41:06.246 --> 41:08.117
-ON A TEMPORARY BASIS.

41:08.248 --> 41:10.685
IF IT DOESN'T WORK OUT, WE'LL
TRY A DIFFERENT APPROACH.

41:10.816 --> 41:12.731
IN THE MEANTIME,
I BROUGHT HER BY

41:12.861 --> 41:14.297
TO SHOW HER THE HEADQUARTERS.

41:14.428 --> 41:15.777
-MORNING, CHIEF.
-CHIEF: MORNING.

41:15.908 --> 41:17.126
-LIEUTENANT BUCHANNON.

41:17.257 --> 41:18.258
-YEAH, YEAH,
YEAH. GOOD MORNING.

41:18.388 --> 41:19.912
WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT THIS.

41:20.042 --> 41:21.783
-NOW MITCH, COME ON,
WE'RE BOTH MATURE ADULTS.

41:21.914 --> 41:23.481
I'M SURE WE CAN TRY TO FIND
A WAY TO MAKE THIS WORK

41:23.611 --> 41:24.830
FOR BOTH OF US.

41:24.960 --> 41:26.527
NOW COME ON, I
WANT A GRAND TOUR.

41:26.658 --> 41:28.529
YOU KNOW YOU LIKE
ME. COME ON.

41:31.010 --> 41:33.142
-[LAUGHING]

41:43.892 --> 41:47.374
-[END THEME PLAYING]
